sipCommonStatsDiscontinuityTimer.name: sipCommonStatsDiscontinuityTimer
sipCommonStatsDiscontinuityTimer.description: The number of centi-seconds since the sipCommonStats were last reset. When the value of this attribute is reset a discontinuity of all of the counters in the sipCommonStats has occured. This should cause the management application to not compute deltas for the current polling interval. These statistics can be reset using the 'clear stats common sip' command on the nCite CLI.
